Denote $a = N(O(N(O(N(O(3))))))$. First we evaluate $N(O(N(O(3))))$. We have $N(O(3)) = N(9) = 2\sqrt{9} = 6$, so
\[a = N(O(N(O(N(O(3)))))) = N(O(N(O(6)))) = N(O(36)).\]Evaluating again, we have $O(36) = 36^2 = 1296$, so
\[a = N(O(36)) = N(1296) = 2\sqrt{1296} = 2 \cdot 36 = \boxed{72}.\]
